criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or non-pregnant female over 18 years of age;

          -  Type B Aortic Dissection;

          -  The left subclavian artery should be reconstructed during the TEVAR procedure.

          -  Patient is willing to provide informed consent and comply with the required follow up
             visits, testing schedule and medication regimen;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Life expectancy of < 5 years;

          -  Patients need open surgery repair for the aortic diseases.
